sentences: Kathleen Aerts (born 18 June 1978 in Geel, Belgium) is a Belgian singer, actress and host.
Aerts was born in Geel, Belgium, on 18 June 1978.

Between 1992 and 1995 she gained experience as a member of the group Wonderful Game and became known for her two participations in the Flemish version of the Soundmixshow: in 1995 she came third with the song Grow A Baby by the Belgian pop group Pop In Wonderland and in 1997 she made it to the semifinals with Chirpy chirpy cheep cheep by Middle of the Road.

Between 1992 and 1995 she gained experience as a member of the group Wonderful Game and became known for her two participations in the Flemish version of the Soundmixshow: in 1995 she came third with the song Grow A Baby by the Belgian pop group Pop In Wonderland and in 1997 she made it to the semifinals with Chirpy chirpy cheep cheep by Middle of the Road.
From 1998 to 2009 Aerts was a member of the successful girl group K3.
Because K3 was originally envisioned as the Flemish version of the Spice Girls, the group was made up of all females in their twenties: Aerts, Karen Damen, and Kristel Verbeke.
K3 achieved success after the release of "Heyah Mama", and in 2002 their manager sold the band to Studio 100.
In 2009 Aerts decided to stop being a member of K3 and to start her solo career.
The single reached the top 3 of the Dutch Single Top 100 in July 2009 and the top 20 of the Ultratop 50 in Flanders.
In November 2009, Aerts released her debut solo album Kathleen in symfonie.
In 2010 she became a member of the De KetnetBand.
The same year she also decided to go back to children's music, releasing a song titled "Boerderij blues" (en.
In 2007 a wax figure of Kathleen Aerts was unveiled in the Madame Tussauds in Amsterdam together with those of the other two original K3 members.
In 2016, Aerts released "Die roos", an adaptation of Ann Christy's hit "De roos", her first single in Afrikaans.
A year later she recorded the single "Afrika", also in Afrikaans, which was also part of the soundtrack of the film F.C. De Kampioenen 3: Forever (2007).

In September 2017, she published her third book: Lilly en Max in de wereld van oma.
In 2020, Aerts participated as Mermaid in the television show The Masked Singer, in which judges must guess the identity of the masked participant.
Kathleen Aerts married Steven van Hoof, a police officer, in 2010.
Their first child, a boy, was born on 26 January 2011.
Their second boy was born in December 2013.
In 2015, she moved with her husband, sons and mother to Paarl, South Africa.
